items.title: Former NSW Labor official admits to exploiting vulnerable children, pleads guilty to dozens of offences
items.author: Jamie McKinnell
items.description: Peter Hansen, a former NSW Labor Party branch secretary and Catholic priest in Melbourne, pleads guilty to more than 30 offences including sex with children in Asian countries.

items.title: Coroner examining Danny Frawley's death urges AFL players to donate brains to science
items.description: It is impossible to tell how much the brain disease CTE contributed to the death of AFL legend Danny Frawley, a Victorian coroner says, as she calls for more research into the condition.

items.title: Amin says tap water burns his skin, so he's been given a bucket for rain
items.author: Sowaibah Hanifie And Edwina Seselja
items.description: A medevac asylum seeker detained in Brisbane's Immigration Transit Accommodation is using a bucket to collect his own rainwater, after a dispute with medical experts over whether it could improve his skin condition.

items.title: Alleged Brisbane sex slave ring operator charged with 13 new offences
items.author: Lily Nothling
items.description: More charges are laid against Matthew James Markcrow who is accused of operating a sexual slavery ring where it is alleged women as young as 17 were drugged and held for prostitution in Brisbane, Queensland police say.

items.title: Mother whose 11yo son died in Texas freeze sues electricity companies for $126 million
items.description: The mother of an 11-year-old boy who died after they lost electricity and heat in their Texas mobile home during last week's freeze files a $US100 million lawsuit against two power companies for gross negligence.
items.content: The mother of an 11-year-old boy who died after they lost electricity and heat in their Texas mobile home during last week's freeze files a $US100 million lawsuit against two power companies for gross negligence.

items.title: Woody Allen labels new documentary on alleged abuse a 'hatchet job'
items.description: The director and his wife Soon-Yi Previn attack a new HBO documentary that re-examines a decades-old allegation that the Oscar-winning filmmaker molested his adopted daughter.

items.title: Ellyse Perry returns from injury to headline Australia squad
items.description: Australia has named its 17-player limited-overs squad to tour New Zealand, with Ellyse Perry and Tayla Vlaeminck returning from long-term injuries.

items.title: Anzac Day events to go ahead in Queensland as Chief Health Officer hopes life can 'return to normal'
items.author: Ashleigh Stevenson
items.description: Queensland authorities are working to "quite rapidly" return to a normal way of life from COVID-19 restrictions, with the Premier announcing ANZAC Day events could go ahead "as normal".

items.title: From 'screaming faddist' to Ogilvie's Scar, Mount Wellington has a long history of grand ideas
items.author: Rachel Edwards
items.description: They've spoken about a cable car for Hobart's Mount Wellington for the past 130 years, so it's not surprising that the latest plan for a "machine on wires" has hit another hurdle.

items.title: Craig Kelly quits Liberal Party to sit on the crossbench, leaves government with one-seat majority
items.author: Georgia Hitch
items.description: The controversial backbencher, criticised for spreading coronavirus misinformation on Facebook, says he decided to become an independent so he can act and speak according to his "conscience and beliefs".
